Reasoning: The paper discusses scheduling strategies for work-stealing systems, which are commonly used in parallel and distributed computing. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the implementation of these strategies in programming languages, which falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper presents benchmarks and optimizations for task parallelism, which could fall under Performance (cs.PF) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of task storage data structures, which could fall under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
